name: fitness_internal
title: Fitness Internal API
description: Used for internal Fitness app data communication

fields.description: Selector specifying which fields to include in a partial response.

key.description: API key. Your API key identifies your project and provides you with API access, quota, and reports. Required unless you provide an OAuth 2.0 token.

oauth_token.description: OAuth 2.0 token for the current user.

prettyPrint.description: Returns response with indentations and line breaks.

quotaUser.description: An opaque string that represents a user for quota purposes. Must not exceed 40 characters.

Capsule.description: Dashboard capsule object - represents a widget to display on the web dashboard.

field.description: A field represents one dimension of a data type.

name.description: Each data type has a unique, namespaced, name. All data types in the com.google namespace are shared as part of the platform.

DataTypeField.description:
In case of multi-dimensional data (such as an accelerometer with x, y, and z axes) each field represents one dimension. Each data type field has a unique name which identifies it. The field also defines the format of the data (int, float, etc.).

This message is only instantiated in code and not used for wire comms or stored in any way.

format.description: The different supported formats for each field in a data type.

name.description: Defines the name and format of data. Unlike data type names, field names are not namespaced, and only need to be unique within the data type.

sourceName.description: Identifies the source of the favorites data, e.g. "web", "mobile", "system_default_v1", etc.

color.description: The user selected color associated with the activity.

fitnessActivity.description: The string form of the fitness platform?s activity, e.g. "walking", "badminton", etc. The list of activities can be found in j/c/g/wireless/android/fitness/constants/Activities.java.

criteria.description: The criteria by which progress an achievement of this goal will be tracked. If unset, achievement must be marked manually.

defaultGoal.description: Default goal created for the user during onboarding.

description.description: Identifies the logic or notification source used to generate the goal. e.g. "Custom goal...", "recommendation:goal:baseline_activity_duration"

descriptionMsg.description: Deprecated. This description should not be surfaced in the UI. Reference to the TransConsole message id for the description.

endTimeMillis.description: The end or due date of the goal. This may be omitted for open- ended or cyclical goals.

id.description: A unique identifier within the user?s account. Simply a hash of currentTime, gaiaID, id generation attempt, and toString() of the Goal object.

parentGoalId.description: If this goal was created as a result of a longer term goal, we reference the parent goal here.

startTimeMillis.description: Most goals are effective immediately so start time is effectively the creation time but this can be used to schedule a more discrete goal like a spinning workout for some time in the future.

templateId.description: Reference to a global template for this goal type (e.g. ?take X steps per day?) which has the localizable message format as well as any preset field value (e.g. DAILY for achievement period in the example above).

timePeriod.description: The period of time over which the goal?s achievement criteria is measured and after which is the goal?s progress is reset.

dataType.description: The xSensor name of the property to be tracked (e.g. ?com.google.step_count?)

maxValue.description: Upper and lower bounds for the property values. Either may be unset depending on the criteria but at least one must be set.

GoalV2.description: Represents a goal, to be contained in a DataPoint, of datatype com.google.internal.goal. The stream will be identified by a datasource id that is a combination of defining characteristics of the goal, e.g. datatype, period, activity, etc; use GoalStreams.getGoalStreamName(). Refer to go/fit-goals for usage examples. Currently used for both storage and service API. Next id: 10

cumulativeObjective.description: The goal objective, depending on which objective type is present, dictates how progress is calculated and which fields are applicable. Exactly one of these are required.

dataTypeName.description: The metric that the goal tracks.

filter.description: List of criteria that the data must meet in order to qualify for counting towards the goal.

recurInterval.description: If this is a recurring goal, amount of time user has to achieve the goal before goal is reset and repeated. Unset if not a recurring goal. Optional.

startTimeNanos.description: The start and end time represent the time at which the goal started to be active or inactive, but this goal may still be edited later on. The timestamps in the data stream represent goal edit timestamps, which will NOT be equal to the start and end time if the goal has been edited. For this reason, the key may not be unique within the data stream.

streamId.description: The stream name under which this datapoint is stored.

fieldName.description: A field name in the given DataType, OR special values ?duration? and ?activity?, which will be extracted from segment. Required.

operator.description: The comparison operator to use on the value, when determining whether the criteria is met. Required.

value.description: The value of the field, to use when determining whether the criteria is met. Required.

frequency.description: Number of segments that pass the filter criteria list.

initialvalue.description: Value at the start time of the goal, which we evaluate towards the objective value.

LocalizableMessage.description: TransConsole message id and its placeholders. Next Id = 7

LocalizableMessagePlaceholder.description: Only one placeholder object for each message placeholder. Each placeholder must contain only one of an int, float, date value, or string and must be named with a string.

distanceMeters.description: Distances formatted as "4.23 km" or "4.23 miles". Note to clients: Always set the distance in meters and specify the length unit. If there is no length unit pref, the default for the user's locale will be chosen.

durationMillis.description: This will be formatted as a short duration like "1 hr 13 min"

name.description: Name of placeholder for messages like "Take {STEPCOUNT} steps" where "STEPCOUNT" is the name.

timeMillis.description: This will be formatted as a short relative date eg. "today", "Wed Aug 26"

MapValue.description:
Holder object for the value of an entry in a map field of a data point.

A map value supports a subset of the formats that the regular Value supports.

creationTimeMillis.description: Timestamp when this notification was generated.

expirationTimeMillis.description: Date/time after which the clients should no longer display this notification.

id.description: A unique identifier for capturing impression and response for this notification. Simply a hash of currentTime, gaia id, id generation attempt, and toString() of the Notification object.

parentGoalId.description: If this notification was generated to support an existing goal we?ll capture that goal?s ID here.

sourceName.description: Identifies the logic used to generate the notification -- possibly with version.

sourceTitle.description: The source title/description are used in the blocked notifications UI.

percentile.description: Percentile expressed as a number between 0 and 100.

NotificationNotificationAction.description: A log of all of the actions the user/client has performed on this notification.

value.description: In millis for time and meters for distance.

sourceName.description: Identifies the notification module; we may want to allow some wild carding so the user can squelch entire categories of notification.

NotificationTimelinePosition.description: Controls where in the timeline a notification should be shown to the user.

specialPosition.description: Show in a fixed position in the timeline.

timestampMillis.description: Show in a specific spot in the timeline denoted by a timestamp.

NotificationTriggerCondition.description: Controls when a notification should be shown to the user.

booleanGservicesKey.description: NOTE: the following trigger conditions were added for Bolt (2015104000+). The app will use the key specified to decide whether to trigger. It will trigger if the value is true, suppress if the value is false.

startTimeMillis.description: A time time interval within which this notification is relevant.

supportedMode.description: Ordinal of FitnessMode.java enum. What modes should this notification be displayed in? If empty, we assume all modes.

NotificationUiModel.description: NotificationUiModels are what the clients use to display. Next id: 22.

additionalMessage.description: Each of these additional messages will appear on separate lines in the body of a notification

additionalMessageMsg.description: Order of these message ids should correspond to those in additional_message. They are used only on the server side for localization.

dismissible.description: Whether or not the user can dismiss this notification (via a swipe or other UI action).

primaryColor.description: If provided, sets the title and button colors. If not provided, we get the color from the icon or activity type.

stateName.description: Identifies this UiModel to be shown when an option is selected. Corresponds to option.value.target_state (if specified).

title.description: Localized messages that're shown to the user

NotificationUiModelButton.description: Describes something the user can click to navigate or perform some action.

includeLabel.description: Whether or not the data values will be displayed on the graph.

includeLegend.description: Whether or not the domain will be displayed to the side of the graph, aka legend.

rangeMaxExtent.description: Specify the range's max extent to be applied to nicing functions.

titleMsg.description: The text to be displayed above this graph.

NotificationUiModelGraphSeries.description: A set of data. NOTE: Our current UX specs require only a single series.

domainMsg.description: Domains contribute to labels and legends.

NotificationUiModelIntent.description: Links to specific places within the clients. Pairs with the INTENT button action. Intents should have a location or a url but not both.

location.description: A feature screen in the client.

NotificationUiModelOptions.description: Options cause UI to be shown giving the user a choice between several options for their goal.

defaultValueIndex.description: The default option that should be selected by the UI

goalTemplate.description: The details for a new goal if we?re recommending a sub goal or replacement goal.

projectedBenefit.description: A quantified benefit expected to be gained by performing this recommendation (e.g. number of steps toward goal)

replacesParentGoal.description: If the goal described in goal_details replaces that identified by parent_goal_id, this should be set to true. If accepted, the parent goal should be cancelled and the contained goal be set in its place.

calorieUnlockTimeMillis.description: Timestamp corresponding to when the user volunteered height, weight and gender info that unlocks calorie data

distanceUnlockTimeMillis.description: Timestamp corresponding to when the user volunteered height info that unlocks distance data

favoriteOtherActivities.description: List of up to seven activities to appear at the top of add/edit activity dialogs. Ordered from most recent use to least recent use. Does not include walking, running, and biking which are always at the top.

startOfWeekPref.description: Indicates the day of the week on which to start a week.

ProfileNotificationSetting.description: For recording user preferences for individual notification types.

sourceTitle.description: Title/description are used in the blocked notifications UI.

durationMillis.description: The summation of the represented activity segments.

endTimeMillis.description: The time the last activity segment ended.

id.description: A unique identifier for a session within the user?s account. Simply a concatenation of the start and end time millis, separated by a '-'.

name.description: A human readable name of the session.

segment.description: The segments that make up the activity.

startTimeMillis.description: The time the first activity segment started.

TimelineSessionActivityInfo.description: Data that is needed on a per-activity basis.

durationMillis.description: The duration of this activity type within the session.

fitnessActivity.description: The ActivityType and raw detected activities that grouped into this Info.

property.description: Properties about this activity type that the UI can use to make decisions about hiding or showing this session.

pathError.description: Issues with the path. You should not show the path in the UX if it has any errors.

placeId.description: This is the GMS PlaceId that can be used to look up details of this location.

endTimeMillis.description: The time the last activity segment ended.

startTimeMillis.description: The time the first activity segment started.

Value.description:
Holder object for the value of a single field in a data point.

A field value has a particular format and is only ever set to one of an integer or a floating point value. LINT.IfChange

fpVal.description: Floating point value. When this is set, other values must not be set.

intVal.description: Integer value. When this is set, other values must not be set.

mapVal.description: Map value. The valid key space and units for the corresponding value of each entry should be documented as part of the data type definition. Keys should be kept small whenever possible. Data streams with large keys and high data frequency may be down sampled.

stringVal.description: String value. When this is set, other values must not be set. Strings should be kept small whenever possible. Data streams with large string values and high data frequency may be down sampled.

gettimelinedata.description: Get data for display in the web frontend.

list.description: Gets the list of web dashboard capsules.

shouldInitialize.description: If there are no capsules, they will be initialized to all available capsules.

list.description: Calls Glycogen to get a list of all active V2 goals.

cancelTimeNanos.description: New effective end time of the goal, defaults to now if unset.

updateCancelCreate.description: Cancel a goalv2 and create another goalv2

list.description: Returns all notifications for a user. If the 'status' parameter is set, only the notifications with a matching status will be returned.

includeStoredNotifications.description: if set, also returns all notifications that have been acted upon by user

list.description: Called by Comaneci and newer clients.

includeStoredNotifications.description: if set, also returns all notifications that have been acted upon by user

annotationDataType.description: DEPRECATED, any values supplied will be ignored. see NonBucketingSessionAnnotator or BucketingSessionAnnotator for supported DataTypes com.google.step_count.delta com.google.calories.expended com.google.distance.delta com.google.heart_rate.bpm

deprecatedIncludePreFillerSessions.description: DEPRECATED, will always default to true.

languageCode.description: DEPRECATED, any value supplied will be ignored.

updateEdit.description: Deletes sessions (from Glycogen) and segments and inserts new.

endTimeMillis.description: Deprecated. This field doesn't have any effect on history deletion.

startTimeMillis.description: Deprecated. This field doesn't have any effect on history deletion.
